renewal and \"slum\" clearance was publicized as a  \"road toward establishing a<br \/>\nbetter standard of city living,\" it was seen by some as little more than a thinly-veiled land<br \/>\ngrab by the wealthy real estate and construction industries. Others&#151;aware of Chicago's<br \/>\nhistory of racial antagonism and the relatively recent large influx of African Americans from the<br \/>\nSouth&#151;perceived that the de facto segregation of the past was being transformed into public<br \/>\npolicy, which the courts finally acknowledged when deciding the landmark Gautreaux v. Chicago<br \/>\nHousing Authority case in 1966 in favor of the plaintiff. Novelist James Baldwin, in a 1963<br \/>\ntelevision interview, famously declared that \"urban renewal means Negro removal.\" In this 1949<br \/>\nletter to architect and urban planner Ludwig Hilberseimer, NAACP Housing Committee chair Faith<br \/>\nRich outlines their concerns. \"To designate a large area for demolition... in a time of critical<br \/>\nhousing shortage... means that the total housing program of the nation becomes geared to keeping up<br \/>\nrents by tearing down houses faster than all agencies combined build them up.\"","resource_full_text":"","resource_types_for_resource_id":"Archival Material","resource_asset_type":"10","resource_image_thumbnail":"..\/images\/Rsrc_TN_001570.jpg","resource_asset_type_label":"","resource_file_size":"0.0 kB","resource_file_size_unformatted":"44.23046875","resource_grade_level":"","resource_curriculum":"","resource_tour":"","resource_file_time":"00m 00s","resource_file_time_unformatted":"0","resource_source_detail":"\"Chicago Looks Ahead: 100 Years of Planning, 1909-2009,\" Case 4, Ryerson &amp; Burnham Libraries, September 29\u2013December 1, 2010<br \/>\n<a href=&quot;http:\/\/digital-libraries.saic.edu\/u?\/mqc,8625&quot;>Link to R&amp;B Archives Digital Collections record<\/a>","resource_tags_for_resource_id":"Chicago, cities, city planning, housing, urban life"